### 4. **Signal and Process Drivers** (delegation pattern)

**SignalDriver** (`/home/bench/repos/tokio/tokio/src/runtime/signal/mod.rs`, lines 91-99):
```rust
pub(crate) fn park(&mut self, handle: &driver::Handle) {
    self.io.park(handle);
    self.process();
}

pub(crate) fn park_timeout(&mut self, handle: &driver::Handle, duration: Duration) {
    self.io.park_timeout(handle, duration);
    self.process();
}
```
Delegates to IoDriver, then processes any pending signals.

**ProcessDriver** (`/home/bench/repos/tokio/tokio/src/runtime/process.rs`, lines 31-39):
Delegates to SignalDriver, then reaps orphaned child processes.

This creates the driver stack: **TimeDriver** → **ProcessDriver** → **SignalDriver** → **IoDriver** → **mio::Poll**

