### 5. **Worker Thread Parking Decision Logic** (`/home/bench/repos/tokio/tokio/src/runtime/scheduler/multi_thread/worker.rs`)

**Main Run Loop (lines 561-628)**:
Workers continuously try to find work in this order:
1. Check local run queue for tasks (line 584)
2. Try to steal from other workers (line 594)
3. **If no work found, park** (lines 600-604)

**Parking Trigger (lines 594-604)**:
```rust
if let Some(task) = core.steal_work(&self.worker) {
    core = self.run_task(task, core)?;
} else {
    // Wait for work
    core = if !self.defer.is_empty() {
        self.park_yield(core)  // park with 0 timeout (polling)
    } else {
        self.park(core)        // park indefinitely
    };
}
```

**Transition to Parked State (lines 1204-1228)**:
```rust
fn transition_to_parked(&mut self, worker: &Worker) -> bool {
    // Workers should not park if they have work to do
    if self.has_tasks() || self.is_traced {
        return false;
    }

    // Transition through idle state machine
    let is_last_searcher = worker.handle.shared.idle.transition_worker_to_parked(...);
    self.is_searching = false;

    if is_last_searcher {
        worker.handle.notify_if_work_pending();
    }
    true
}
```

